HEADWORD: instrumented
<hw>in"stru*men`ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having
instruments attached for the purpose of measuring conditions while under
observation; -- said of a person under medical observation or a machine
whose performance is being tested.</def>⟦br⟧
